WEBVTT

00:06.680 --> 00:09.650
- He's back everyone.
- How I've missed this.

00:11.080 --> 00:13.010
Larry, wait for me!

00:13.580 --> 00:15.810
Mind your head,
or I'll jump on it!

00:17.350 --> 00:19.520
- I'm coming in!
- No!

00:21.600 --> 00:25.500
- Still gruesomely pea brained.
- Still with your bullshit.

00:27.020 --> 00:30.530
Spiros's wife had an affair
with Basil?! Silly Baz?

00:30.560 --> 00:33.650
Oh don't.
I feel so guilty about it.

00:34.330 --> 00:37.510
Leslie was only trying
to help Spiros and I be together.

00:37.560 --> 00:40.410
He's been cycling around
desperately trying to find Spi...

00:40.510 --> 00:42.060
- Hello, darling.
- Hello.

00:42.990 --> 00:45.800
Well, my travels were eye-opening,
thanks for asking.

00:45.950 --> 00:47.500
Ah Gerry!

00:47.650 --> 00:50.730
I was approached in Athens
to work for British Intelligence.

00:51.550 --> 00:53.610
- I said no, of course.
- Or did you?

00:53.740 --> 00:55.680
- Yes, I did.
- I'd love to be a spy.

00:55.710 --> 00:57.360
Can you put my name forward,
please?

00:57.390 --> 00:58.560
- You'd start a war.
- No, don't.

00:58.590 --> 01:01.660
I don't need to be a spy,
I combat idiocy through my art.

01:02.170 --> 01:04.750
I thought we could put on a play,
to celebrate me being back.

01:04.780 --> 01:07.720
- Let's do Porgy &amp; Bess!
- No, we're too white.

01:08.250 --> 01:09.280
I've written a play.

01:09.310 --> 01:13.170
It's 'The Odyssey' adapted to tell
our story since we came to Corfu.

01:13.200 --> 01:15.270
Well, I'm not doing it.
The theatre's daft.

01:16.170 --> 01:19.220
That's a shame, I had you down
for Odysseus, the hero.

01:20.160 --> 01:22.350
I need a distraction, I'll play him.

01:24.140 --> 01:27.170
Well, I did bring you all here
on an epic Greek journey,

01:27.200 --> 01:28.290
which we are still on.

01:29.140 --> 01:30.300
- Very good.
- Thank you.

01:31.340 --> 01:35.080
Oh, just to update you:
Europe's on the brink of war.

01:35.260 --> 01:37.340
Another reason to do
a rip-roaring theatrical satire

01:37.380 --> 01:39.150
on the folly of battle.

01:39.180 --> 01:41.280
Yes, but this is the safe end
of Europe.

01:42.190 --> 01:46.300
- Hardly. Italy's invaded Albania.
- That's only two miles over the water.

01:47.160 --> 01:48.300
Well we're all ignoring it.

01:48.330 --> 01:51.340
We're all back together
and we're not going anywhere.

